==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*σκανδαλίζω / skandalizō / skan-dal-id'-zo

===Etymology===
To “[[scandalize]]”; from [[σκάνδαλον]]; to [[entrap]], that is, [[trip]] up (figuratively [[stumble]] [transitively] or [[entice]] to sin, apostasy or displeasure): 

===Verb===
'''σκανδαλίζω'''

# (make to) [[offend]].

